title: oooooooOOOOO My
body:
I need a victim for an experiment!! What characters face should I paint and possibly destroy? XD

I got my gouache in!

It feels like an acrylic paint (which I am very familiar with) but blends like a watercolor. 

I only did a small test tonight. I added a little bit to my current painting to help push the face a bit more, but I already added so many colors and layers I think it would have defeated the purpose of adding a ton of gouache other than for some high lights and to lighten a few areas. 

I can see where it can be great for hair and flowers. Hair is really difficult to paint in watercolor. Flowers are a pain in general. XD 

I want to do a test painting of an actual portrait in gouache with a basic watercolor under painting to get started, kind of like what I would do for an acrylic painting. 

so who should I do a test portrait of?

Look who came back! the little butterfly!
Lucius never imagined this, now he wants it dead.

Anyway I draw Ash with Luci because I don’t wanted anyone alone (and I failed) and because they are good friends so why not? She don’t bother him, so he don’t mind be with her

Also they are in a place out of the festival, just like the old drawing of Lucius with the butterfly.

summary: "Youthful Melanin" by ZYI - Pen, color pencil, marker on bristol paper  A birthday portrait for a close friend of mine from a...
caption:
“Youthful Melanin” by ZYI - Pen, color pencil, marker on bristol paper

A birthday portrait for a close friend of mine from a memory captured amongst one of our many rendezvous. This piece is to embrace his melanin because, despite society’s impression of him,  he is the embodiment of divine black masculinity, both tender and robust.

Instagram/Twitter/Facebook: @eyeofzyi

Photographer: @pvrexdreams

Model Instagram: @whyansworld
